BUMARO.definition: 1. young man below or at the age of puberty and usually though not necessarily unmarried; boy.
BUMARO.cross_reference: BARO. 2. young male of the water buffalo or cow; pony

BUMARO.definition: to be near or at the age of puberty: said of the male.

BUMBA.definition: to pump, especially a pump well (POSO).

BUMBA.eng_example: The airplane will bomb our house.
BUMBA.ilok_example: Bumbaen diay exoplano daytoy balay tayo.

BUNAG.definition: to transport, to carry from one place to another.
BUNAG.eng_example: Will you please transport our belongings?
BUNAG.ilok_example: Bunagen yo man dagitoy alikamen mi?

BUNOG.definition: the BUKTO fish when at its largest size.

BUNOT.definition: the outer husk of the coconut; coir.

BUNTIEK.definition: the young of the fish called DALAG.

BUNTON.definition: a small hill, hillock; a small hill built by termites.
to lay or place in a pile, pile up, heap in abundance.
to be placed in a pile; to pile up.

BUNUBON.definition: seedling, a plant grown from a seed for transplanting.
to grow plants from seeds for transplanting; to sow seeds for seedlings.
BUNUBON.eng_example: We can sow seeds for seedlings now.

BUNYAG.definition: to baptize someone especially in church.

BUNYAG.eng_example: It is the old priest who will baptize my child.
BUNYAG.ilok_example: Daydiay lakay nga padi ti mangbunyag ti anak ko.

BUNYAG.definition: to give or bestow on as name or alias.
BUNYAG.eng_example: This is what he bestowed on me as an alias.

BUNGA.definition: 1. fruit; result. 2. child -a term of endearment used especially in literary works.

BUNGA.eng_example: Our mango tree is now bearing fruits.

BUNGA.definition: to bear, result to, lead to.
BUNGA.eng_example: That mango tree of yours will bear many fruits.
BUNGA.ilok_example: Adu ti bungaen dayta mangga yo.

BUNGA.definition: to have or develop a sty.
BUNGA.eng_example: The man’s eye is developing a sty.

BUNGABONG.eng_example: He announced his intention to run as a candidate.
BUNGABONG.ilok_example: Inbungabong na ti gandat na nga agkandidato.

BUNGAW.definition: having one or both testicles swollen or enlarged; having scrotal hernia.

BUNGDOL.definition: with tipless or blunt horn, as a cow or water buffalo.

BUNGLUG.definition: having the stench of rancid oil, lard, etc.

BUNGON.definition: to wrap, bundle, package; to bundle up.
BUNGON.eng_example: Bundle up your child well for it is getting cold again.
BUNGON.ilok_example: Bungonem nga nalaing dayta anak mo ta lumamiis manen.

BUNG-OR.definition: to become swollen and tender due to an injury or infection.

BUNGSOT.definition: to cause to rot, become spoiled, putrid, foul.

BUNGULAN.definition: a kind of yellow, spotted, fragrant banana.

BURAK.definition: to break into bits, crush, shatter, crumble.
to be crushed, shattered, broken into pieces.
to shake in order to collect the fish, shrimps, crabs, etc. caught in (the fagot).
BURAK.eng_example: I shook the fagots and collected the fish, shrimps, crabs, etc. caught in them.

BURANG-IT.definition: to raise one’s bottom or buttocks, to set oneself in a position with the bottom or buttocks up.
to set  place (someone  something) with the bottom  buttocks up, to set  place upside down  bottom up.

BURARAWIT.definition: a long slender branch; a pendulous top of the bamboo.

BURAS.definition: to pick or gather (fruits), especially when ripe or mature.

BURAY.eng_example: Give your pity to us willingly.

BURAYOK.definition: to flow profusely, to gush out.
BURAYOK.eng_example: The blood of his wound gushed out.
BURAYOK.ilok_example: Nagburayok ti dara diay sugat na.

BURBUR.definition: down, soft fluffy hair, furry hair.

BURBURAN.definition: 1. a kind of spaniel, poodle or Pekinese dog with long, thick wavy hair. 2. a kind of shaggy blanket.

BURBURTIA.eng_example: I will tell you a riddle, Bert.

BUREK.eng_example: The water is already boiling. 2. to foam, froth, lather, bubble.

BURIAS.definition: a young hog usually less than a year old, shoat.

BURIK.definition: a bird, a cock or rooster, with variegated plumage.
to engrave something on, to put an engraving on.
BURIK.eng_example: It was he who put an engraving on my ring.
BURIK.ilok_example: Isu ti nangburik toy singsing ko.

BURIK.eng_example: Engrave my name on this ring of mine.
BURIK.ilok_example: Iburik mo ti nagan ko ditoy singsing ko.

BURIS.definition: loose bowel movement, watery excrement or feces.
to have loose bowel movement, to have diarrhea.

BURISANGSANG.definition: brown sugar in loose form with big clods in it.

BURO.definition: fish, meat or fruit preserved in salt.

BUS.definition: to go by bus, to take or ride on a bus.

BUSAT.definition: 1. first sale of the day. 2. first sale of the day of a particular merchandise.

BUSBUS.eng_example: He was the one who used up all their properties.
BUSBUS.ilok_example: Isu ti nangbusbus iti amin nga kukua da.

BUSBUS.definition: to loosen, slacken; to make loose or slack.
BUSBUS.eng_example: Why are you making the binding of the box loose?
BUSBUS.ilok_example: Apay nga busbusem dayta galut ti kahon?

BUSBUS.eng_example: Tighten the band of the box so that it will not become loose.
BUSBUS.ilok_example: Irutem dayta galut ti kahon tapno saan nga mabusbus.

BUSEL.definition: 1. flower bud of pistillate flowers. 2. young coconut, melon, squash, etc.

BUSI.definition: to pop, as corn or rice.

BUSINA.definition: horn, especially that of a car, truck or carriage.
to sound a horn at or for; to summon, drive away, or attract the attention of by sounding a horn.
BUSINA.eng_example: Sound your horn to drive away those water buffaloes on the road.

BUSLON.definition: to waste; to use much more than necessary.

BUSNAG.definition: light-colored, fair in complexion: said of a person.

BUSOR.eng_example: He was the one who contradicted me.

BUSSOG.definition: to fill oneself with food, to satiate oneself with food.
BUSSOG.eng_example: Fill yourself with food for we are going far.
BUSSOG.ilok_example: Agbussog ka ta adayo ti papanan tayo.

BUSSOG.definition: to fill or satiate with food, to feed until full.
BUSSOG.eng_example: Don’t fill that dog with food so that it will not go to sleep.
BUSSOG.ilok_example: Saan mo nga busbussogen ta aso tapno di nga maturog.

BUTBUT.definition: to put a hole on; to puncture.

BUTEG.definition: like mucus: said especially of the meat of young coconuts or betel nuts.

BUTENG.definition: to be afraid of, scared of, frightened by; to dread, fear.

BUTBUTENG.eng_example: He went to the cementery without fear.
BUTBUTENG.ilok_example: Awan ti butbuteng na nga napan idiay sementerio.

BUTBUTENG.eng_example: Don’t scare me for I may have a heart attack.
BUTBUTENG.ilok_example: Saan nak nga butbutengen ta dinto atakien nak ti sakit ti puso.

BUTBUTENG.definition: frightening, scary, alarming; causing fear or fright.

BUTILAW.definition: a protrusion of the uterus into the vagina.

BUTINGGAN.definition: wild tomato whose fruits are small, round and smooth skinned.

BUTO.definition: 1. penis. 2. style of the pistil. 3. tongue of a bell.

BUTON.eng_example: He pressed on something like a button.

BUTONES.eng_example: Button your clothes before you come out.
BUTONES.ilok_example: Agbutones ka pay sa ka rumuar.

BUTONES.eng_example: She will put buttons on my shirt.

BUTONG.eng_example: They crowded like flies around the one selling fish.
BUTONG.ilok_example: Binutong da nga kasla ngilaw daydiay aglako ti ikan.

BUTTIOG.definition: pot-bellied, having a protuberant belly: said of adult persons especially the male.

BUTTOT.definition: a person who is excused from doing manual work or house chores.

BUTTUAN.definition: corn, a local hardening and thickening of epidermis (as on toe).

BUYA.definition: to see, watch, look at, view.

BUYAT.definition: to pour out (water or any other liquid).
BUYAT.ilok_example: Ditoy mo nga ibuyat dayta danum.

BUYOG.definition: to follow, comply with, fulfill, do accomplish.
BUYOG.eng_example: Remember to fulfill your promise to us.
BUYOG.ilok_example: Laglagipem nga buyogen ti karim kadakami.

BUYOK.definition: fetid, having a bad smell; stinking.

PABUYON.definition: to ask someone to find the location or situation (of a lost object or missing person or animal) by divination.

BUYUBOY.definition: a kind of cup or dipper made of coconut shell.
